Hull City have made an offer to take Carl Jenkinson on a permanent deal.

The 22-year-old can leave Arsenal and was initially set to leave on loan.

Arsenal signed Calum Chambers from Southampton on Monday in a £12million deal that could rise to £16m, and it is clear Jenkinson is now surplus to requirements. They have also signed right back Mathieu Debuchy from Newcastle for £10m.

